 199:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c **** /**
 200:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * @brief  Update SystemCoreClock variable according to Clock Register Values.
 201:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         The SystemCoreClock variable contains the core clock (HCLK), it can
 202:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         be used by the user application to setup the SysTick timer or
 203:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * configure other parameters.
 204:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 205:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * @note   Each time the core clock (HCLK) changes, this function must be called
 206:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         to update SystemCoreClock variable value. Otherwise, any
 207:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * configuration based on this variable will be incorrect.
 208:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 209:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * @note   - The system frequency computed by this function is not the real
 210:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           frequency in the chip. It is calculated based on the predefined
 211:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           constant and the selected clock source:
 212:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 213:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           - If SYSCLK source is HSI, SystemCoreClock will contain the
 214:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * HSI_VALUE(**) / HSI division factor
 215:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 216:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           - If SYSCLK source is HSE, SystemCoreClock will contain the
 217:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * HSE_VALUE(***)
 218:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 219:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           - If SYSCLK source is LSI, SystemCoreClock will contain the
 220:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * LSI_VALUE
 221:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 222:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           - If SYSCLK source is LSE, SystemCoreClock will contain the
 223:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * LSE_VALUE
 224:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 225:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *           - If SYSCLK source is PLL, SystemCoreClock will contain the
 226:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * HSE_VALUE(***) or HSI_VALUE(*) multiplied/divided by the PLL factors.
 227:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 228:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         (**) HSI_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32g0xx_hal_conf.h file
 229:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * (default value 16 MHz) but the real value may vary depending on the
 230:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * variations in voltage and temperature.
 231:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 232:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         (***) HSE_VALUE is a constant defined in stm32g0xx_hal_conf.h file
 233:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * (default value 8 MHz), user has to ensure that HSE_VALUE is same as the real
 234:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *              frequency of the crystal used. Otherwise, this function may
 235:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *              have wrong result.
 236:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 237:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *         - The result of this function could be not correct when using
 238:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * fractional value for HSE crystal.
 239:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  *
 240:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * @param  None
 241:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  * @retval None
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccpAUc7C.s 			page 6


 242:Core/Src/system_stm32g0xx.c ****  */
